{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 I've long needed a quick way to create a tape slowdown, tape stop, tape stop effect. I usually use a free plugin for this - [b][url=https://kilohearts.com/products/tape_stop]kHs Tape Stop[/url][/b], and for a faster speed I wrote a simple script that does the following just for this fx: Along the length of the razor edit creates an envelope item, and in that area sets the stop parameter to "on" mode to activate it in the desired range. And also sets the stop time relative to the length of the razor-edit. You can disable the automatic length setting by clearing the flag in the editor here to false: local razorLength = true --this flag To quickly create the desired slowdown effects without auto-setting. Also, the exact same script will be attached to this script soon, but it will be placed inside an athame and set the envelope points. Demo link - https://imgur.com/ZdGodGG\par}
